5 per person\n\nLearn pra... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 19\n						7:00pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Nisan Rosh Chodesh Circle\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join us for our monthly Rosh Chodesh gatherings\, an opportunity to come together and get rooted in our Jewish tradition and the natural land cycles. Each session is crafted to correspond with the new ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 23\n						11:00am - 1:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Babies on the Farm!\n\n						\n											\n\n					Welcome to our drop-in group for babies and their parents! We will meet to shmooze\, play and enjoy some music and Boichik bagels. You are welcome to come late or leave early. This is meant to be an i... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 24\n						7:00pm - 9:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Finding Your Freedom – a PJ Library Passover Program for Parents\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Jamie Greenwood\, somatic life + leadership coach\, for an interactive workshop exploring the Passover theme of freedom and how we can reclaim that freedom in our day-to-day lives for greater conne... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 26\n						6:30pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Releasing the Pharaoh Within: A Kundalini Yoga Workshop Inspired by Astrology\n\n						\n											\n\n					Many of us have external freedoms\, but consistently struggle with various levels of dread and worry. Supported by the story of Passover\, we'll be exploring how to shift these patterns. Along with Yoga... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 27\n						5:30pm - 6:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Tot Shabbat w. Mimi Greisman!\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Urban Adamah and Mimi Greisman for Tot Shabbat on the farm where little ones and their grown-ups come together to celebrate\, sing\, and make new friends! With joyful songs\, playful movement\, and i... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 27\n						6:30pm - 8:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Kabbalat Shabbat\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join Urban Adamah for our signature Friday night service! Through song\, poetry\, movement\, and silence we’ll journey together from our week of doing into our day of being. All are welcome. No Hebrew ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						March 29\n						4:00pm - 5:30pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Passover Family Festival\n\n						\n											\n\n					Join us on a journey through the seder\, as we celebrate Passover with a hands-on\, interactive experience for the whole family! Explore exciting stations inspired by the Haggadah\, with activities\, craf... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n			\n			\n\n				\n					\n						April 4\n						9:30am - 6:00pm\n					\n				\n\n\n\n				\n					\n						Shabbat Day-Long Mostly Silent Meditation Retreat With Adam Berman\n\n						\n											\n\n					No Previous Meditation Experience Required\n\nAt its deepest level\, Shabbat invites us to stop\, to release the habitual momentum of striving\, fixing\, producing\, and proving. It asks us to step out of ... \n\n					Learn More\n				\n			\n		\n\n		\n\n	\n		\n		Next Page
